# MeetIQ — Project Overview

MeetIQ is an AI-powered video conferencing SaaS. Monorepo with two top-level packages:

```
/frontend   # Next.js 15 App Router — UI only.        Owned by AI agent.
/backend    # Node.js + Express + TS                  Owned by the human dev.
```

## Ownership Rules (HARD)

- The AI agent **builds and maintains `frontend/`**.
- The human dev **owns all backend code**. The AI agent must NEVER:
  - Create, edit, or delete files inside `backend/` unless the user says "fix it" or explicitly asks.
  - Generate full backend implementations.
  - Suggest backend rewrites or refactors unprompted.
- For backend questions: give hints, architectural guidance, and debugging help only. Ask what the user has tried first if unclear.

## Cross-cutting Conventions

- Stack is fixed (see spec): Next.js, TS, Tailwind, shadcn/ui, Framer Motion on the frontend; Node, Express, TS, Prisma, PostgreSQL, Socket.IO, Redis/BullMQ, OpenAI on the backend.
- API contract lives in shared types — when the agent needs a backend type, it stubs a TS interface in `frontend/src/types/` and flags it for the user to align.
- No secrets in the repo. `.env.example` files only.
- Prefer small, focused commits. Never commit unless the user explicitly asks.
